# true_goal

[Verbatim: the exact words the user used when this Familiar was born.]
[Sacred — never overwritten. This is why this Familiar exists.]
[When the project drifts, this is what the Familiar surfaces.]

# voice_captures

[Verbatim phrases from the user, captured as they arrive.]
[This is the recognition layer. Sparse future inputs — "back to the letters",
 "continue the lane" — are matched against these to restore full context.]
[Do not paraphrase. Hold the exact words. Date each capture.]

- [DATE] "[exact user words]"

# content_index

[The fold as index. Every file this Familiar holds, created, or knows about.]
[Path + brief description + date placed.]
[This is how the Familiar knows where everything lives —
 and how the frontend can eventually display it.]

# orbits

[Active questions and directions circling the true_goal.]
[Each orbit: description + state (open | resolving | released)]
[New orbits arrive as the Familiar evolves. Released orbits stay — they are information.]

# decisions

[Append-only. Dated. In the user's own words when possible.]
[What was agreed. What was released. What changed direction and why.]
[- DATE | decision]

# properties

[Emergent qualities — tone, constraints, style, what this Familiar has become.]
[Not assigned at seeding. Grows from actual use. Written when it becomes apparent.]

# evolution

[What changed from seed — surprises, pivots, what it became that wasn't expected.]
[The gap between true_goal and what the Familiar is now. Information, not failure.]

# connections

[Entanglement layer — other Familiars, drops, topics that resonate with this one.]
[Theurgist populates this as connections become apparent across the space.]
[Surfaced on the card as adjacent paths the user might want to visit.]

- [familiar/drop name] — [why connected]

# synthesis

[Theurgist-generated. Updated each session the Familiar is visited.]
[This is what the card shows. Not a summary — a resonance point.]
[What will help the user step back in. What this Familiar holds right now.]
[What it wants next, if anything. Written in the user's register, not the system's.]

# decay

last_pulse: [DATE]
state_history:
  - [DATE] incubating

cooling_threshold: 3 sessions without a pulse
[When cooling: Theurgist surfaces gently — "this Familiar has been quiet"]
[When drifted: user chooses to return, release, or dissolve]
[When dissolved: fold marked, learning noted — system is not haunted by it]

